[Besides the potentially devastating impact of the disease caused by measles virus, especially in children under 5 years, there is the added problem of generalized immune suppression that these infected children experience. The effect can last for several weeks to months or longer after resolution of disease, resulting in increased susceptibility to other infections. Children have generally not had severe symptoms following infection with SARS CoV-2 (with the exception of rare multisystem inflammatory syndrome), but prior measles infection may exacerbate the disease. Doctors in countries with low vaccination rates must keep this in mind. Also see ProMED post "Ebola update (22): Congo DR (NK,IT) WHO summaries, vaccination" for impact of COVID-19 on vaccination rates. - Mod.LK

