[2] Kyrgyzstan
Date: Wed 27 May 2020
Source: Akipress [abridged, edited]
https://akipress.com/news:642340:717_measles_cases_recoded_in_Kyrgyzstan_since_year_start/


Measles incidence has been recorded in Kyrgyzstan since the beginning of 2020. To date, a total of 717 cases of measles have been reported, the Health Ministry said.

Measles cases are being registered in Jalal-Abad, Chui, Osh, Batken regions and in Bishkek and Osh cities. The numbers of this infection have decreased significantly since March 2020.

One-year-old children had the highest rates of infection with measles (52.2%); 14.5% refused vaccination, 5.3% had a medical exemption to vaccination; 2.2% were among migrants.

